  "text": "Lucas Gouveia / How-To Geek | CL Shebley / Shutterstock Jackery Solar Generator 1000 $698.99 $1299.99 Save $601 The Jackery Solar Generator 1000 package gets you a 1000Wh power station and a 200W portable solar panel for charging all for one low price.  A solar generator is one of those things that you don't think you need until you actually do one day. Jackery makes some of the best ones, and now, its Explorer 1000 V2 is currently almost half off—knocking an insane $600 off its MSRP. Jackery's Explorer 1000 V2 solar generator has an MSRP of $1,400. Right now, however, you can get one for $699. While these kinds of products are never actually at their MSRP all the time, $699 is an insane price considering the package you're getting here. Related This pack features a 1070Wh LiFePO4 battery, offering a neat 1500W continuous output (with a 3000W surge peak) to power a wide range of appliances, from refrigerators and microwaves to laptops and medical equipment. It weighs around 23.8 lbs, and it's notably lighter and more compact than its predecessors and other generators in Jackery's range (if this is still too expensive for you, Jackery also has some considerably cheaper alternatives). This particular unit boasts Jackery's ChargeShield 2.0 technology, providing multiple charging modes, including an emergency super charge that can reach 100% in just one hour via AC. It also supports solar charging, making it a sustainable power solution. With multiple AC, USB-A, and USB-C ports (including a 100W PD port), it can charge several devices simultaneously. This is the lowest price we've seen to date for this particular model, and considering the bang you're getting for your buck, it's a must-have if you've been looking for a perfect off-grid companion or if you simply need a backup power source in the case of an emergency. Make sure to buy this before this deal is gone, though.",
